From 77cc8818ff72e3425e59566fbcb3ec03f1c6bd40 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zach Taylor <zctaylor.work@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 08:35:07 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 45/48] Add warp.ui.setStatusItem(id, item): plugin status
 pills in the tab bar (oh-my-warp)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A plugin can now publish small, themed pills that live in the tab bar
(right of the leader indicator) — for live status the user should glance at:
a build state, an active session count, ccusage today's spend, a CI label.

JS API:
  warp.ui.setStatusItem("ci",     { text: "CI ✓",      kind: "success", command: "ci.open" });
  warp.ui.setStatusItem("queue",  { text: "queue 3",   kind: "warn" });
  warp.ui.setStatusItem("ci",     null);          // remove
  warp.ui.setStatusItem("queue",  { text: "" });  // also removes (empty text)

Item shape: { text, kind?, tooltip?, command? } where:
  - kind     info | success | warn | error | accent — picks an ANSI theme color
             so the pill tracks the active terminal theme.
  - command  optional plugin command id; clicking the pill dispatches
             WorkspaceAction::RunPluginCommand(id) — same path palette items
             and keybindings take, no new routing.

Identity is (plugin_id, item_id) so one plugin can publish several pills
(e.g. branch + CI + queue) and update each independently.

Wiring:
  - PluginStatusItemsModel singleton (app/src/workspace/plugin_status_items.rs,
    always compiled — empty when plugin host isn't built in).
  - New PluginAppRequest::SetStatusItem + PluginHostEvent::SetStatusItem; the
    Workspace subscribes (existing subscribe_to_plugin_host fan-in) and updates
    the singleton.
  - Workspace observes the singleton -> tab-bar re-renders.
  - render_plugin_status_items called from render_tab_bar_contents, right after
    the leader indicator.

Capability: 'ui' (same as toast / showMarkdown / showPalette / prompt).
